This directory contains the project header files shared across the firmware modules.

Current headers are used to separate the application into small parts instead of keeping everything in a single `main.cpp` file.

Typical contents:
- application entry points and shared state declarations
- IMU reader interfaces
- data logger interfaces
- serial console interfaces
- configuration constants and shared data types

In this project, source files in `src/` include these headers to keep the firmware modular and easier to extend with future features such as activity classification, BLE, and mobile sync.
